### Thematic Clusters Revealed by Index

- **Probability wars** — frequency vs. Bayesian debate is
  a recurring spine of the book; figures from Pascal to
  Thorp to Black/Scholes all appear under this heading
- **Money as risk technology** — money, derivatives, and
  numeraire are treated as a unified theory, not separate
  topics; the index cross-references these extensively
- **Risk managers as creators (not just measurers)** —
  the "unspeakable truths" cluster signals Brown's
  contrarian core: VaR is not risk, risk managers
  should create risk, firms should be allowed to fail
- **Gambling → finance pipeline** — Thorp, Kelly, poker,
  sports betting, blackjack all cross-referenced with
  Wall Street and quant methods; gambling is treated as
  the honest ancestor of financial risk-taking
- **Quant revolution** — old-school vs. new-school quants;
  three camps; stock market crashes and; rocket scientists;
  migration to Wall Street
- **IGT vs. MPT** — Investment Growth Theory is Brown's
  proposed alternative framework to Modern Portfolio Theory,
  appearing as a distinct index cluster with its own CAPM

